<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-27T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-27T17:00:00-05:00" n="267" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.01A/176: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-27T18:00:00-04:00">June 27,
                                    1942—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>167. Your 316, June 26. Please tell Prime Minister that delay in
                            furnishing advisers has in no way been due to lack of interest on part
                            of this Government. On contrary, Department has been and is continuing
                            to make every effort to locate suitable men. We fully appreciate
                            importance of this question and hope to achieve concrete results in near
                            future. Prime Minister will understand that demands of our own war
                            effort make it doubly difficult to secure services of men with high
                            qualifications needed for such positions.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>